org.antlr.intellij.plugin.parsing

Class TokenStreamSubset

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.antlr.v4.runtime.BufferedTokenStream
      • org.antlr.v4.runtime.CommonTokenStream
        • org.antlr.intellij.plugin.parsing.TokenStreamSubset
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.antlr.v4.runtime.IntStream, org.antlr.v4.runtime.TokenStream

    public class TokenStreamSubset
extends org.antlr.v4.runtime.CommonTokenStream
    This TokenStream is just a CommonTokenStream that can be cut off at a particular index, such as the cursor in an IDE. I had to override more than I wanted to get this to work, but it seems okay. All parsers used within the plug-in should use token streams of this type.
